column16: Description
Comment
Light industrial asset. Vacated in 2022
Grey warehouse boxes with limited office share. Good location in LI area right at the highway. Decent size. Good tenants (Elgiganten, Carlsberg, Pilkington)
Urban logistics portfolio of 14 assets in Helsinki metropolitan area. Assets have good micro locations next to the main highways. NOI €5.9m, occupancy 98%, WAULT 3.5 years.
Heathcare portfolio of four properties, anchored by the leading private healthcare operators (Terveystalo & Mehiläinen) and the City of Vantaa. Strong micro locations, WAULT 7.5 years, 95% occupancy.

Residential multifamily property located in the Triangle Region in the centre of Denmark. The property is divided into two sites and totals a GLA of 6,186 sq m divided on 84 modern units. Nymarkshaven is located in the northern part of the city of Fredericia in an established residential area near daily necessities, daycares, schools and leisure activities.

Two fully leased properties in Tygelsjö, Malmö, rented by Malmö municipality. The preschool(completed in June 2019 by Skanska) has a 15 year WAULT. The LSS residence (been completely renovated in two phases, 2014 and 2022) consist 700 sqm of residential space and a 250 sqm barn, leased until 2030 with a 5-year extension

Potential sale of a container self-storage provider, the operations including some IOS properties accross Sweden. Prinsens Lager is a Swedish container self-storage provider offering cost-effective storage solutions. They have 25 sites today of which 50% are freehold tenure. 1,700 containers on current sites with potential to expand with c. 600 containers on current sites.

Newly built warehouse/logistics property, completed in 2023 (93% warehouse and 7% office), features 14 gates, including 11 loading docks and 4 terrain gates. Fully leased on a 10-year non-terminable lease.The Purchaser will acquire the property in its entirety, including both the initial 4,546 sqm section and a planned 2025 extension of 3,898 sqm, all under a fully constructed and leased arrangement with Stock Group A/S

Located in the Kolla Parkstad area in Kungsbacka Municipality, the property currently has three completed buildings (Houses A-C) with a total of 87 apartments, as well as a fourth building (House D) under construction, scheduled for completion in spring 2025, which will add an additional 25 apartments.

Mixed use property (52% warehouse/industrial & 32% offuce ) located in Tumba with proximity to Tumba centrum, E4 highway and public transport. 42% government backed rent. Alfa Laval, currently the largest tenant (52% of the leasable area), has announced their intention to relocate part of their operations to Flemingsberg, unlocking an opportunity to reposition the property into a regional hub for government agencies, Additional building rights of 180,000 sqm available

The property consists of 81,529 sqm of freehold land and buildings with a rentable area of 8,217 sqm. It has a fully indexed triple-net lease agreement. The highway (E4) passes by just outside of the property

A 10 year sale-and-lease back transaction in the Hørsholm life science cluster. Apart from office space, the Property comprises fully equipped laboratories, administrative and storage space and an auditorium. DKK 4m deposits avaiable (6 months rent)

The property is located in the new sustainable district of Bunkeflostrand, Malmö, with plans for residential and commercial development. The area is strategically positioned to connect rural and urban parts of Malmö, offering a mix of housing and amenities. The development aims to create a new local center in Bunkeflostrand.

A cutting-edge logistics park at the Port of Malmö spanning 38,813 sqm, with a project cost of SEK 506 million and an estimated market value of SEK 834 million. The project features BREEAM certification and solar energy use, with a profit margin of SEK 328 million.

A JV opportunity to develop logistics properties near key locations, starting with a 37,584 sqm facility at the Port of Gothenburg. The project, designed with sustainability and efficiency in mind, has a total cost of SEK 590 million, an estimated market value of SEK 864 million, and a projected profit of SEK 274 million.

The project involves two existing office buildings in Örnsberg that are undergoing detailed planning for expanded uses, including offices, residential units, commercial purposes, and non-disturbing industry. The entire surrounding industrial area is also part of the same plan and will be developed with new housing. The detailed plan is expected to be reviewed and adopted by mid-2026, allowing for the addition of two to three residential floors to the buildings, which would provide lake views. The properties currently generate a net operating income of around SEK 16 million with historically low vacancy rates (below 5%).

Five properties with a sale-leaseback arrangement, featuring 10-year lease agreements. The tenant is responsible for all operating costs and ongoing maintenance.  The tenant provides a parent company guarantee for all lease agreements

Centrally located near the market square, with 81.4% of shares in Kiinteistö Oy Sampotalo for sale, offering control over a 9,683 m² commercial center and 155 parking spaces. The primary tenant (Tokmanni) contribute to 64% of the rental income with a lease valid until 2030. The debt-free asking price is €6,000,000.
Two light industrial properties in Glostrup and Taastrup, with an expected finder's fee of 1.25%.

The property is centrally located in Jakobsberg, Järfälla, with excellent access to public transportation. Built in 1953, it has been upgraded over the years and offers potential for further value-enhancing renovations. The property includes both residential units and commercial spaces. The rent increase for 2024 is 5.9%, with a planned increase of 4.2% for 2025

The Nordic Forum property is a modernized mixed-use asset featuring a diverse tenant mix, including a 25-year lease with anchor tenant Mogotel Hotel Group for a premium hotel. The asset has undergone significant investments, totaling SEK 491 million, enhancing its appeal with amenities such as a gym, restaurants, and co-working spaces. It boasts strong environmental credentials with a BREEAM In-Use rating of "Very Good
Located in the Vilsta industrial area of Eskilstuna, the property benefits from proximity to major transport routes and a strategic position in one of Sweden's key logistics hubs

Fully leased property located in Avedøre Holme, the property provides easy access to the E20 motorway (2 km) and is just 10 km from Copenhagen. The property features 16 strategically placed gates and is part of a cadastral plot divided into two commercial owner-occupied apartments
A light industrial property of approx. 2,000 m2 with the possibility of extending the warehouse with approx. 1,300 m2.

Stenmjölet 3 is located in the Vinsta industrial area, a strategic location in western Stockholm poised for transformation into a mixed-use urban district. The property includes a diverse mix of tenants from retail, production, and office sectors. It offers significant potential for future development and rental income adjustments

A completely newly constructed portfolio of environmentally certified buildings with triple-net leases. Approximately 90% of the portfolio is leased to Wiretronic, Ahlberg Cameras (Lifco), Hitachi, and Entrack (Lantmännen). All these companies are highly capitalized and strong tenants. For Wiretronic, where construction is currently underway, there is an option to expand the building by an additional 4,000–5,000 sqm as the company is growing rapidly. A lease agreement will be made for this expansion
Besqab Syrénbersån is located in Ultuna Trädgårdsstad, 5 km south of central Uppsala. The new development project consists of 137 well-designed, Swan-labelled apartments in various sizes and layouts.
Retail / LI property located in Linnakallio, Pirkkala. Leased to two tenants KX-Center Oy and R-Tech Suspension Oy

The main tenant is also the seller. The property is owned by a separate company, enabling a tax-advantaged company transfer. Royal Unibrew and Logster pay below-market rents, providing potential for rent increases. Insulated cold storage areas (Teknisk Agentur’s warehouse and Logster’s space) could see higher rents with added heating. Some uncertainty remains due to the missing lease agreement for the new tenan
Skyline Airport Hotel. Located near Helsinki Vantaa Airport, this hotel offers proximity to business parks and the planned Moomin Theme Park.
This property is a centrally located, renovated historical commercial building in Jyväskylä, featuring well-known tenants like Kesko and Fitness24Seven.

Barkarbystaden Kvarter 3, known as the "Signaturkvarter," is located next to the new main square and metro station in Barkarbystaden, offering  356 rental apartments with an average unit size of 45 sqm.. The project, backed by Derome and Reliwe with comprehensive guarantees, is set to commence in Q1 2025 with completion targeted for 2027. It presents an investment opportunity with a projected yield of 5.0% and a forward funding rate of 6.0%.

Umami Park is located just 150 meters from the metro station, offering  308 rental apartments (average unit size 43 sqm) in three buildings. The area benefits from excellent transportation links and a variety of nearby services. The project is designed with a high sustainability profile, including energy class B and Environmental Building Silver certification. Completion expected in 2026

Located in a central area of Nacka (Orminge), the Solhusen project features 147 newly constructed rental apartments (average unit size 52 sqm). The development emphasizes environmental sustainability, adhering to the standards for the Miljöbyggnad Silver certification
Located in a central area of Nacka (Ektorp), the project includes 87 apartments (average unit size 48 sqm), with 10 designed as group housing for individuals under the Social Services Act.
The project involves developing 40,000 sqm of gross floor area (BTA) in Spånga. The goal is to start construction on the first building in 2025.

The project includes 169 newly completed apartments in central Nacka. The project boasts excellent access to public transport and amenities, enabling residents to reach central Stockholm in just 20 minutes as of today. A new metro station is planned to open in the area 2030. Premium product with high price expectations (and high negotiated rents).
Located in the western part of Turku near Länsikeskus, the property is a commercial building with a leasable area primarily for retail, including tenants such as Ahlsell Oy and Maalarienmestarien Oy.
Padel hall located in Räntämäki, Turku. The building was constructed in 2022.
Mixed use property located in Vaasa. Main tenants are Euromaster, Hoplop, Posti and Grano. Four different buildings.

Project Sol portfolio comprises three modern logistics properties strategically located in Örebro, Borås, and Vansbro, Sweden. Notably, the property in Vansbro features energy-efficient enhancements, including solar panels.

The project includes 169 newly completed apartments in central Nacka. The project boasts excellent access to public transport and amenities, enabling residents to reach central Stockholm in just 20 minutes as of today. A new metro station is planned to open in the area 2030. Premium product with high price expectations (and high negotiated rents).

Centrally located light industrial property with significant development potential. The property is strategically positioned near Uppsala city center and major transport routes. Rental income is MSEK 2.7, unspecified whether it is triple net. There is a mutual 3 months mutual notice period and with a waiver from security of tenure agreement in place. 10,590 sqm is currently leased to Riddermark Bil AB
Forward retail big box investment opportunity in Kuopio. Construction time 12 months, forward funding or forward purchase. Tenants will be Gigantti, Power and Jula.

The project is located in the Myren area in central Strömstad and consists of two neighbourhoods, Linden and Häggen. It consists of 256 new apartments. The project was sold to Runar Vatne in 2021, however he was not able to take over when the project was finished in 2023. Ongoing discussions between parties, but likely a new sales process in 2025. The project is valued at 400 mSEK.

Located in Ballerup, these properties offer excellent connectivity to Greater Copenhagen, making them ideal for logistics.The portfolio includes two well-established logistics properties with significant leasable areas.
Three buildings, total lettable area 23,618 sqm. In total 28 tenants and leased area some 17,000 sqm. The main tenant Metalpower Oy (8,131 sqm) has fixed 10-year lease agreement

The property is located in Riksten, which offers good communication options with convenient access both by car and public transport. Rullbanan 2 consists of four buildings which houses 110 residential units. Inflygningen 1 contains one building (Building D) with 105 residential units. It is located right across the street from Rullbanan 2.

Located in the new district of Storskogen, about 2 km south of central Enköping, this project offers significant residential development opportunities. They have building rights for 339 units with a GFA of 35,676 sqm.

Located in a prime last-mile location in Greater Copenhagen, Priorparken 839 is a high-quality light industrial property with strong anchor tenants. The property offers multiple value-creation opportunities and benefits from excellent accessibility and infrastructure.
Residential portfolio comprising diverse projects across Denmark, showcasing development and operational potential.

The project has an excellent location at the centre of Greater Copenhagen right next to the motorway grid. PostNord has been a tenant since 1997, and signed a 10-year contract in August 2024, with a termination notice of 12 months.
A portfolio of 60 properties and 300 tenants, positioned in some of Sweden's largest and most dynamic regions: Stockholm, Gothenburg, Malmö and Mälardalen.

Situated in Nacka, Stockholm's rapidly urbanizing suburb, the property offers excellent transport links and modern facilities, including energy-efficient systems and commercial spaces. The rent for the residential leases is fixed and cannot be increased until January 2027.
The portfolio consists of eight properties with 975 residential units across the greater Gothenburg area. Out of the 975 apartments, 558 are completed and 417 are under construction.

Located in Valby, a prime district in Copenhagen, Project Emerald offers a rare development opportunity with excellent connectivity and a flexible development framework, allowing for significant residential and commercial development potential. 75% of the property are residential units while the remaining 25% are commercial units
Single-tenant asset with a double-net lease in Hämeenlinna. Was in a semi off-market in 2024, now the lease has been extended and the deal is in structured process.

Located strategically in Uppsala's Kungsängen district, the property benefits from proximity to major transport routes and Uppsala Central train station, making it ideal for last-mile logistics and consumer-focused operations. The property also offers significant development potential with flexible zoning allowances.

Located in Finnslätten, ca. 4 km from central Västerås. The area is known for its concentration of high-tech companies and innovative industries. The property is fully used by Veho today, and will be leased back to the seller simultaneously at the time of the transaction.
Located in the growing Greater Gothenburg area, Project Crane offers a high-quality residential portfolio with excellent public transport access and proximity to key amenities.
Located with views over Lilla Värtan and Kungliga Djurgården, the property is close to public transportation and local amenities.
Car retail / light intustrial property located in Vantaa. Main tenant Tesla. Occupancy rate 100% and WAULT ca. 8.4 years.

The Project Sol portfolio comprises three strategically located logistics properties in Sweden, fully leased to strong tenants with long-term agreements. These modern facilities are situated in key logistics hubs, providing excellent connectivity and ensuring stable income streams through 100% occupancy and CPI-indexed rents.
The properties are centrally located in Fagersta and Norberg, offering easy access to local amenities and public transport.

An undeveloped property in Alelyckan, Gothenburg with building rights for light industrial purposes. The 6,708 sqm plot allows for a max building height of 10m and 50% utilisation according to the zoning plan.

column6: DEAS Property Fund Finland I Ky
column16: Light industrial/warehouse/office portfolio with 4 properties. Three of the properties are located in Aviapolis, Vantaa, and one in Kerava. Freehold plots. 16 tenants.

The property is a distribution centre fully let to VELUX A/S. The warehouse space has 7.5-14m ceiling height and complementary office space. It is leased with an NNN-lease with a 15-year non-terminability (incl. two years' notice).

This is a development project located in a prime area of Copenhagen. The Rosewood property will include 85-95 hotel keys and 5-10 branded residences. The development benefits from its proximity to major attractions and the financial district.

The portfolio consists of five industrial and office properties located in Åkersberga and Uppsala. The two properties in Åkersberga is situated in areas designated for future residential development by the municipality, including the Kanalstaden project, which aims to create 3,000 new homes. The portfolio is located near Stockholm, Uppsala and Arlanda as well as transport links.

The property is in Lunda industrial area, Stockholm. It is fully leased to Sodexo AB, which operates a medical equipment center under contract with Region Stockholm. The location offers good transport connections, including proximity to Förbifart Stockholm and public transit.

The property is a fully leased last-mile distribution center in Greater Copenhagen, serving as a regional hub for PostNord. It features a sorting facility with 40 loading docks and EV charging stations. The location provides connectivity to Copenhagen and southern Sweden via major motorways.

The portfolio consists of four properties in Stockholm, combining residential, office and commercial spaces. The properties are located in growing urban areas. The indicative price for Hökarängen is 45-50 kSEK/sqm and 50-55 kSEK/sqm for Hammarby Sjöstad

column6: Arlandastad Group AB & Bake My Day Holding AB
column16: A built-to-suit food production facility leased to Bake My Day on a long-term 15-year contract. Located in Arlandastad area near Stockholm Arlanda Airport. The tenant has made significant investments in energy efficiency and food production standards to ensure sustainable operations.

A multi-let automotive service and sales facility in Arlandastad, featuring 11 tenants. The asset includes a mix of car services, sales, and parking, with further development potential of approximately 9,000 sqm.

The portfolio consists of two newly developed properties in Arlandstad, Sigtuna, leased to Bankomat and OneMore AB. Bankomat has a 15-year contract. The property being leased to OneMore AB is under development with expected completion in August 2025.
Söderhall 5:10 is an industrial development site in Vallentuna, north of Stockholm, adjacent to the E18 highway.

The Project Tygelsjö portfolio consists of two fully leased properties in Malmö, both rented by Malmö municipality. The portfolio includes a modern preschool built in 2019 as well as an LSS residential property that was renovated in 2014 and 2022 to meet specialised care requirements.

column6: L-Å Eveberg Fastighetsutveckling AB & Berith Margareta Eveberg
column16: Sävedalens Torg is a fully leased mixed-use property located in Sävedalen, on the border between Partille and Gothenburg. The property has strong anchor tenants, including Västra Götalandsregionen and Triumfglass. The property consists of retail, office and restaurant spaces, and a small warehouse.
A light industrial property located next to the E20 highway in Greve. The property is fully leased to Delicate A/S on a long-term contract.

Fuglekvarteret is a large-scale urban redevelopment in Copenhagen, transforming a former industrial site into a residential and mixed-use neighbourhood. The project will be completed in multiple phases, featuring a mix of residential units, retail spaces, social housing, and a dedicated parking facility.

Circle House is a large-scale mixed-use development in Kokkedal, Fredensborg, featuring residential units, commercial spaces, and a parking facility. The project is being developed in two phases, with full completion expected in 2029.

Tumba Skog is a large-scale residential development located in Botkyrka, Sweden, approximately 1.5 km from Tumba Centrum. Magnolia plans to buil around 348 new homes in this area, consisting of rental apartments and townhouses, with construction beginning in Q1 2026 and expected completion between 2028 and 2029.

Project Doppingen is a portfolio of four light industrial properties in Norrköping, located near the E4 highway and Norrköping harbor. The properties have flexible zoning regulations for further expansion.

Skinderskovvej 32 is a vacant industrial property in Herlev, Greater Copenhagen. The site has some soil contamination due to past industrial use, and any remediation costs will be the responsibility of the buyer.
JM is developing 205 residential units in Söderdalen, to be completed in 2026-2027. The project consists of 11,293 sqm residential area and 237 sqm commercial space.
The project consists of 97 townhouses in Greve. Turnkey delivery is expected in August 2025.
Two properties in Sätra and Bredäng with a total of 137 apartments. A building permit exists for the creation of additional residential area in Sätra, approx. 200 sqm of new space.
A residential and commercial development in Hvidovre, Denmark. The project includes 188 residential apartments, commercial spaces for retail and cafes, and a raised courtyard with shared facilities.

This portfolio consists of three retail parks in Nyborg, Haslev, and Aalborg Nord, developed by Innovater A/S. The properties include a total of 32 rental units with major tenants such as JYSK, Elgiganten, Coop, and Harald Nyborg.

Portfölj Huddinge consists of four commercial properties located in Huddinge, with a mix of industrial, retail, and office spaces. The portfolioio benefits from strong connectivity to major highways, ensuring access to central Stockholm and surrounding business districts.

Portfölj Västberga consists of five properties positioned in Västberga, Stockholm. The portfolio includes a mix of industrial, office, and retail spaces. With connectivity to major transport routes, the properties offer redevelopment potential.
Älvsjö Konsumenten 2 is an office property situated along Huddingevägen in Älvsjö, near Älvsjö Station and Stockholmsmässan.

column6: Byggservicegruppen i Göteborg AB, Joakim Olsson, Henn Soppi, Anders Svensson, Lars Svensson
column16: Mölndal Kusken consists of two properties strategically located in Åby, Mölndal, close to the E6 highway and major transport routes. Kusken 6 comprises office and industrial spaces, while Kusken 8 includes a fully leased gym with long-term agreements.
A residential development project comprising 132 apartments across four buildings, with completion expected by the end of Q1 2026.
Droppen is a newly developed residential property in the Hyllie district of Malmö, featuring 108 apartments and a ground-floor commercial unit. It is positioned just minutes from Hyllie Station.

An industrial and logistics property in Alby Industriområde, just three minutes from the E4/E20 highway. The property features a 1,300 sqm warehouse with up to 10 meters of ceiling height and office spaces. Fully vacant.
A residential development project in Täby, consisting of 236 built-to-rent apartments with a mix of studio, one-, two-, and three-bedroom units. Storsala acts as both developer and project manager.

A built-to-rent residential development in Märsta, with 94 apartments and 87 parking spaces, designed to include studio, one-, and two-bedroom units. The mixed-use project also contains approximately 400 sqm for commercial use, such as shops and restaurants. Storsala will be actively overseeing the development.
A residential development in Solberga, featuring 99 built-to-rent apartments ranging from studios to four-bedroom units.
A built-to-rent residential development in Orminge, Nacka, consisting of 177 apartments with a mix of studios, one-, two-, and three-bedroom units.

Project Hamlet is a last-mile logistics portfolio in Denmark, featuring 12 assets across the Capital Region and Triangle Region. The portfolio has a strong tenant mix, high occupancy, and an ESG roadmap aimed at long-term sustainability improvements.

Valseholmen 10 is a light industrial property located in the Avedøre Holme business district. The property will be fully vacant in May 2025. The sale price depends on whether the property is sold stabilized with tenants (DKK 50-52 million) or vacant (DKK 46-48 million).
Vallmovallen is a planned residential project in Vellinge, consisting of two multi-family buildings with 102 apartments. There will be a retail unit on the ground floor and 22 parking spaces.

Project Bluebell is a large-scale Battery Energy Storage System (BESS) investment opportunity led by Flower. The portfolio includes operational and under-construction BESS assets across Sweden, with additional development rights for 2.8GW of projects across multiple European countries. The joint venture structure allows an investor to acquire a majority stake in the AssetCo while leveraging Flower’s expertise in trading and optimisation.
A project in Aarslev consisting of 68 SFR units. Expected completion in October 2026.
Logistics asset located next to Helsinki Airport in Vantaa, Finland. The property was built in 2008 and has been fully occupied by RCK Finland Oy since its completion.

Residential project with c. 85 rowhouses. Local plan expected in Q2 2026. Trim, the developer, is in negotiations with the land owner to secure an option on the plot. Project will be built in two phases, with the project completed as of Q3 2027.

Residential project in Jyderup consisting of c. 165 rowhouses. Building permit is expected in Q3 2025. Trim, the developer, is in negotiations with the land owner to secure an option on the plot. The project will be built in five phases and has an expected completion in Q3 2027.

Trim, the developer, is in negotiations with the land owner next to the plot we intent to build on in Kalundborg, to see if we can secure additional area. Upon receiving more information we will evaluate the opportunity, taking into considerations that we do not want to be overallocated in one city.
Residential project in Helsinge. Trim, the developer, is in discussions with Troldeutvikling, option owner. Project will be built in five phases, with the entire project completed as of Q4 2027.

Project Bavne Ager consists of 42 senior rental apartments designed under the "Boliger for Livet" concept, ensuring access to nearby care facilities. The development is located in Gilleleje. The project is being delivered as a turnkey investment.

Grönfinken is a fully leased social infrastructure property in Borås, Sweden, featuring a mix of municipal services and residential units. Borås Stad has signed a new 15-year lease. The asset offers future development potential with the possibility of adding additional floors for municipal or residential use.
Residential development project in central Sollentuna, Stockholm, consisting of 309 rental apartments.
An LSS opportunity with 20 properties primarily located in southern/central Sweden. Most of the properties are built after 2020. Mainly Humana and Nytida as tenants.

Project Grace is a fully leased office property situated in central Stockholm, at the intersection of Kungsgatan and Sveavägen. The property's flagship tenant is Sweden’s leading co-working operator, IOffice.

Helseholmen 1 is a development opportunity in Avedøre Holme. The land plot spans 15,000 sqm with an assumed 70% density ratio, supporting a mixed-use development of logistics and office space. Holding period is assumed to be four years, with a deal start in July 2025. The expected return is 1.7x MOIC and 24% levered IRR.

Project Green Oak is a residential development opportunity in the district of Rågsved, approximately 13 km from central Stockholm. The portfolio consists of three properties. Estimated building rights for further development is estimated to encompass 6,691 sqm.

Last-mile logistics and light industrial portfolio located around Ring Road III in Helsinki Metropolitan area. The portfolio includes 14 assets with significant upside potential through rent reversion, leasing of vacant space, and optimization of unused building rights. With a stable, diversified tenant base and 99% of cash flow inflation-hedged, the portfolio offers strong income security and long-term growth opportunities.
Markan 6 is a residential property located in Hägernäs, Täby, consisting of four buildings with a total of 52 apartments. The property was built in 2010 and has a site area of 12,658 sqm.

column6: Egetbo Invest ApS, Brudebakke Holding ApS
column16: Petuniaparken is a newly developed residential project in Aalborg SØ, consisting of 48 single-story row houses and semi-detached houses. The project is divided into two phases, with the first phase expected to be completed by the end of 2025 and the second by late 2026.

Sundheden is a development project in Aalborg Ø, located next to the upcoming University Hospital and Aalborg University. The project consists of 14,100 sqm of residential properties, and 15,500 sqm of commercial spaces.

A large-scale development opportunity with zoning in progress and power infrastructure upgrades planned. The site benefits from proximity to a 150kV substation. Currently, the zoning process is ongoing with the local plan being prepared and expected to be finalised by 2025. Supply capacity up to 250 MW from Q2 2027.
Fully leased hotel and concert hall. Elite Hotels and Växjö Municipality are the long-term anchor tenants with fixed CPI-linked rents.

Cultural, congress, and conference facility in Karlstad. Fully leased to publicly backed tenants, including Karlstad Municipality and the Swedish Consumer Agency. Development potential, including 9,500 sqm of  building rights.
Skanska’s portfolio consists of three residential projects in Stockholm, Göteborg, and Helsingborg. Possible to bid on the whole portfolio or in parts.

Tingberget is a large-scale residential property located in Kungsbacka, with a walking distance to rail connections. The property consists of 295 apartments, and additional development rights for expansion.
The property consists of two buildings, constructed in 1969 and 2000, with mixed office, workshop, and showroom spaces. The current tenant, Quickpoint A/S, is responsible for operating expenses.

Project Hamlet is a last-mile logistics portfolio in Denmark, featuring 12 assets across the Capital Region and Triangle Region. The portfolio has a strong tenant mix, high occupancy, and an ESG roadmap aimed at long-term sustainability improvements.

Project Kvarts is a fully let light-industrial property located in Veddesta, Järfälla, within Stockholm County. The property has a WAULT of 4.6 years and is leased to three tenants operating in metalwork, manufacturing, and industrial innovation.

The property is the only cargo terminal at Turku Airport, anchored by FedEx and DHL. It is situated in a strategic airside location with no comparable alternatives nearby. It underpins critical air freight operations in southwestern Finland.

Timotejen 20 is an office property in Telefonplan, Stockholm, originally built in 1913 and later transformed into office spaces. Stockholm city center ia a 15-min drive away. It is anchored by Stockholm Municipality, contributing 15% of rental income.

Byamannen 2 is a residential property in Botkyrka, south of Stockholm, consisting of six buildings with 246 apartments and 43 parking spaces. Completed in 2019/2020 by Titania. The property has received multiple awards for sustainability and residential development.

Naverland 26 is a fully leased investment property in Glostrup, Denmark, situated on a 7,000 sqm plot with three buildings, two of which are occupied by the seller. The site includes a historical trichloroethylene contamination from the 1950s, with remediation costs covered by the regional environmental authorities.

Project Sigvid consists of 10 residential properties located in Södra Sofielund, Malmö, with a total of 172 apartments and six commercial units. The properties are well-connected, situated near public transportation and within cycling distance of Triangeln station. The portfolio offers potential for value-add opportunities, including attic conversions and optimization of vacant spaces.

column6: J & S Fastigheter i Sverige AB
column16: Consists of four residential properties in Älmhult. The properties are well-maintained, featuring modern heating systems and low vacancy rates.
Two properties in prime logistics areas with easy access to major highways and transport nodes. They were completed in 2022.

Located at Norra Bantorget in central Stockholm, comprising 23 residential apartments and six commercial units. The property offers a total leasable area of 2,731 sqm, with a significant portion dedicated to residential use.
Residential investment opportunity located near Turku CBD, featuring two apartment buildings completed in 2023. The properties are equipped with sustainable features such as solar panels.

Forward purchase deal presented to us by Preservia. Two SFR projects (to be developed and sold by Obos) with an expected completion in Q1 2027. The deal value of 38,559 SEK/sqm includes financing costs.
SLK Pipeline with 5 properties across Denmark. The properties consist mainly of townhouses and some apartments.
The SLK Portfolio comprises six properties across Denmark, primarily consisting of townhouses. One of the properties is a residential care institution.

A portfolio of five properties located across Denmark, focusing on senior communities and residential developments. The properties are positioned in Holbæk, Tisvilde / Vejby, Næstved / Fensmark, and Roskilde. The developments are designed to cater to the growing demand for senior housing, with a mix of senior communities and residential row houses.

Soldaten 1 is a school property under construction in Viksäng, Västerås, designed to accommodate 408 students from preschool to grade 6. The development includes facilities such as a sports hall, kitchen, dining area, and library, with completion expected in 2026. The property benefits from excellent transport links and is situated in a family-friendly area with anticipated demand for school placements.
Missionsskolan is located in Lidingö, Stockholm, established by the Swedish Missionary Society in 1908. The property includes educational facilities (4,386 sqm) and residential units (1,052 sqm).

An opportunity to join GrupoLar's new PBSA investment platform as a strategic equity partner, aiming to deliver 4-5 PBSA assets totalling c. 2,000 beds. The platform's primary focus is Warsaw, targeting 3-4 assets, with the remaining assets planned for Krakow and/or Wroclaw. Portfolio underwritten on 5.85% exit yield.
The Tingberget portfolio comprises four residential properties in Kungsbacka, with renovation potential. The properties are located 20-min from Gothenburg city centre.

A residential project located in Alsike, Knivsta. The project includes 230 rental apartments, 450 sqm of commercial premises, and 159 parking spaces, with expected completion by 2027. The development is positioned near a new commuter train station.
A residential portfolio located in Oxelösund. It consists of 192 apartments which are divided into nine properties.

Pederstrupvej 84 is an industrial and office property located in the district of Ballerup Business Park. The property is fully leased to Struers ApS, a metallographic solutions company, under a 15-year lease agreement.

A residential development project in Ösmo, Nynäshamn, with potential for constructing various housing types, including row houses and multi-family dwellings. The detailed plan has gained legal force, and there are existing building permits.

A residential development project in Hørsholm that will consist of approximately 37 homes with private parking and gardens. The project is located within walking distance to shopping facilities and public transport.

Parkhus is a residential development project located in Roskilde. Recent regulatory changes have allowed for a more diverse mix of housing types and reduced parking infrastructure. Expected construction cost of c. DKK 23,000 pr sqm (ex VAT and land). The projected sales price is around DKK 40,000 pr sqm.

An office and industrial property located in the Eriksbergs industrial area of Botkyrka Municipality. This is a sale leaseback process where Lotus Maskin & Transport AB is flexible regarding future solutions within the property and is open to signing a lease agreement ranging from one to five years
Logistics asset located in Örebro. The property is fully leased to Dollarstore. It has an EPC A rating and BREEAM Excellent certification.

Project Ruby is located in the Etu-Töölö district of Helsinki. Originally constructed as a telephone exchange in 1915, the building has since been converted to house five apartments and office premises, and also includes a parking garage. The transaction concerns 70% of the shares.

Consists of two residential properties located in Hammarbyhöjden and Bagarmossen in Stockholm. The properties offer a mix of 1, 2, and 3-room apartments, benefitting from proximity to public transport and green spaces.

Project Ellenbogen 13 & Tjuren 11 consists of two mixed-use properties located in central Malmö, offering residential, retail, and office spaces. Ellenbogen 13 is situated in the Gamla Staden area, while Tjuren 11 is located in the Limhamn district.
Project Tuve is an industrial property in the Tuve area of Göteborg, fully leased to Volvo. The site includes a car service center, damage workshop, and additional facilities.

Project Haven is a social infrastructure asset in Helsinki, Finland, featuring an unbreakable 15-year lease with Validia, the leading provider of disability services in Finland. The property is located next to Pohjois-Haaga train station and Ring Road I. The asset is undergoing extensive refurbishment to convert it into a care property.

Project Alder is a residential development in Alsike, Knivsta, offering 230 rental apartments. The project includes commercial premises and parking spaces, located near a future commuter train station. The development is designed to meet Miljöbyggnad Silver certification standards and includes significant green spaces.

A warehouse/logistics property located in Nørager, Denmark with direct access to the E45 motorway. The property includes 33 loading docks with ramps and is partially leased to Nopa. The previous broker company marketed the property at over DKK 80M.
The portfolio consists of twelve properties in Bålsta, Håbo Municipality, with a total of 19 buildings, including two under construction.

Kollekollevej 39 is a residential development in Værløse, designed to accommodate a mix of first-time homebuyers and downsizers seeking community living. The project is located near public transport and green spaces.

A salmon infrastructure facility in Finnmark, Norway, fully leased to Grieg Seafood Finnmark AS. The facility is undergoing a strategic upgrade to increase production capacity and produce larger post-smolt.

Three development opportunities totaling up to 22,000 sqm of residential space. The first sub-projects are already underway, with construction of 7,700 sqm of rental apartments and 11,000 sqm of private care and senior housing scheduled to begin in 2025.

Comprises two retail assets located in Täby and Lund, Sweden. Both properties are strategically positioned with access to major roads, reaching over 200,000 households within a 20-minute drive. The portfolio features well-performing tenants secured by long leases with a WAULT of 7.9 years. The properties can be sold together or separately.

column6: Sigillet Bostäder, VM Måleri AB Larsson & Robertsson, Västsundet El Förvaltning
column16: Located in the Bellevue area of Gamlestaden, Göteborg, the property offers a residential setting with easy access to services and transportation. It is fully leased, including residential units and a small storage space, with parking facilities. The property has been actively managed and regularly renovated to maintain high standards

Project Hirundo is a residential portfolio located in Hjulsta, Stockholm, featuring 1,194 apartments across 14 properties. The area benefits from good transport connections, including proximity to the metro and major highways. According to Sindi's platform, the area is facing significant socioeconomic challenges.
Project Metropolitan comprises eight urban logistics assets in Gothenburg and Stockholm. The portfolio benefits from a diversified tenant mix and significant ESG enhancements.
Logistics facility in Marieberg, Örebro. The asset is single-let to Dollarstore, serving as the tenant's main warehouse, with a long lease term remaining.

Project Blue comprises 19 care properties across 16 cities in Finland. The portfolio is anchored by three tenants, including Validia, Mehiläinen, and HUS. The properties are intended to be sold as a portfolio, and not as individual assets.

Klyvären 1 and 3 are located in Västra Hamnen. The properties offer a mix of residential, retail, and office spaces. The area is well-connected with public transportation and is a sought-after location for both living and working.

The Småhusportfölj in Lekebergs kommun consists of 13 residential properties with good commuting options to Örebro and Karlskoga. The portfolio is fully leased with a low turnover rate and an active waiting list. The properties are primarily small houses built with investment support.

Located in central Gothenburg, the property primarily consists of office space, complemented by residential and commercial units. It has significant rental uplift potential, with approximately SEK 4.4M in uncapitalised market rent. Once Västra Götalandsregionen vacates the premises, a total of 2,770 sqm will become available.
The properties are located in Västra Hamnen, Malmö. Both properties feature energy-efficient designs and offer a mix of residential and commercial spaces, catering to a diverse range of tenants.

A property in Bandhagen, Stockholm, consisting of 72 residential units. The property offers development potential with zoning in progress for an additional 33 apartments, expected to be approved in early 2026. Currently, 26 units are vacant.

Located in central Gothenburg, the property primarily consists of office space, complemented by residential and commercial units. It has significant rental uplift potential, with approximately SEK 4.4M in uncapitalised market rent. Once Västra Götalandsregionen vacates the premises, a total of 2,770 sqm will become available.
Located in Holmen in Copenhagen. The building, originally constructed in 1892, has previously been used for educational and cultural purposes, but is now vacant.

Aalborg N is a retail destination in the North Denmark Region, featuring a mix of supermarkets and specialty stores. The site benefits from good accessibility due to its proximity to major highways and serves a large catchment area. Expected completion Q2 2027.
Located in central Denmark, Bjerringbro has strong industrial and retail presence. The site is positioned near key amenities and transport links. Expected completion Q3 2026.

Brande is known for its industrial sector. Construction of the first phase of the project will be finalised in Q3 2025 where tenants will take over. There is room for a second phase with potentially 2,750 sqm.

Ballerup is a suburban hub in the Greater Copenhagen area, known for its strong transport connections and business parks. The retail project has attracted significant tenant interest due to its  location. Expected completion Q4 2026.
Nyborg is a transport hub on Funen, offering good accessibility via the Great Belt Bridge. The retail park is located to serve a large customer base from nearby towns. Expected completion Q1 2025.
The retail park benefits from good logistics and proximity to existing shops. The project was finalised in Q4 2024.
A new residential development in Ishøj Municipality, located in Greater Copenhagen. The project includes 20 row houses and 121 apartments.
Engrækkerne is a newly developed residential community in Kokkedal, featuring 136 terraced houses. Stages 1 and 2 were completed in March 2024, and the final stage was completed in December 2024.

Comprises of 61 apartments: 46 on free-market rent and 15 youth housing units, along with 336 sqm of commercial space. The turnkey project will be delivered fully or nearly fully let. Potential pricing flexibility due to the seller being under pressure from the bank to sell.

Consists of two portfolios, each owned by a different fund: NSF IV includes 13 properties and NSF V includes 19. The properties are spread across Sweden. The seller does not want to split the portfolios, so buyers need to either acquire both portfolios or all the properties in one of the portfolios.

Comprises two retail assets located in Täby and Lund, Sweden. Both properties are strategically positioned with access to major roads, reaching over 200,000 households within a 20-minute drive. The portfolio features well-performing tenants secured by long leases with a WAULT of 7.9 years. The properties can be sold together or separately.

Tune Midtby is a new residential development located at Industrisvinget 1 in Tune, within Greve Municipality. The project consists of 4 buildings, each with 2 floors and a total of 48 apartments, offering a variety of unit sizes from 62 to 91 sqm.

The property at Jernholmen 34C is undergoing a warehouse extension that will increase the total lettable area from 3,590 sqm to 4,721 sqm. Currently, the building comprises 315 sqm of office space and 3,275 sqm of warehouse space. Post-extension, the warehouse area will grow to 4,406 sqm, while the office space will be unchanged.

The portfolio includes strategically positioned industrial and logistics properties adjacent to major roadways and transport infrastructure across Finland. It offers more than 41% NOI upside potential.

Forward commitment opportunity for a 28,000 sqm logistics project in Nykvarn, Stockholm South. No tenant in place; seller takes on construction and financing risk, buyer takes leasing risk through forward commitment.

Project Lotus comprises 11 properties located in micro-locations within the Helsinki Metropolitan Area. The properties benefit from good public transportation connections and a wide variety of nearby services.

A portfolio of four properties located in suburban areas of Stockholm, including Gamla Enskede, Hägersten, and Bromma. Includes a total of 50 apartments, 27 of which are rented on short-term contracts.
Project Swan is a residential project located in Bro Mälarstad. The project comprises 199 residential units across five buildings and has a normative rent of SEK 1,550 per sqm.

Project Svenljunga is located in the Moga industrial area of Svenljunga. The property is fully leased to Star Trading under a 10-year agreement. It benefits from good transport links, including proximity to major roads and regional markets.

Hammerhaven is a development project located in Roskilde, featuring 46 rental apartments, 15 public youth housing units, and 4 commercial units. The project is designed with a focus on sustainability and is certified to DGNB Gold standards.
Sankt Jakob 14 is located in Lund city center. The property consists of 12 apartments, 941 sqm of retail space and 973 sqm of office space.
Project Primula consists of three properties located in Kungsbacka and Nyköping, comprising a preschool and two LSS facilities. These properties are fully leased to municipal and foundation tenants.
Located in Karlstad, Triangeln 1 and Trombonen 1 offer 390 residential units. The properties are positioned near Karlstad University. Both properties are equipped with solar panels.

column6: F. Holmström Fastigheter i Nynäshamn AB
column16: Hamn & Berg comprises two properties located in Nynäshamn and Åkersberga, consisting of residential and commercial spaces. The portfolio comprises 121 residential units and 4,031 sqm of commercial space. Both properties are well-connected to Stockholm.

Project Noma comprises five logistics properties located in key transportation hubs in Copenhagen, Aarhus, and Horsens. The portfolio is fully occupied, and offers significant rental upside potential due to current under-rent conditions.

Sigtuna Stadsängar is a residential development project with good connectivity to Uppsala and Stockholm. The project includes plans for 84 residential units and 54 parking spaces. It is situated just 15 minutes from Arlanda Airport.

Located in central Uppsala, Svartbäcken 46:16 is a fully leased industrial and commercial property with development potential. Initial studies suggest potential for residential conversion with a possible volume of 6,000-7,000 sqm.

Amaron Commercial Properties is raising capital to invest in logistics, warehouse, and industrial properties in the Öresund region, with a strong focus on sustainability. Their current fund conssits of 33,386 sqm of industrial properties. The offering is structured as an equity-based Alternative Investment Fund (AIF), listed on the NGM Main Regulated Nordic AIF, with an expected annual return of 12–17% plus a 4% dividend.

Located in Toftanäs, Malmö, Kamaxeln 2 is an office and industrial property built in 2001. It is fully leased to Peab Lokal AB until 2028. The property benefits from good transport links and proximity to major highways 29.

Grafiten consists of three properties located in Trollhättan, offering a total leasable area of 19,767 sqm. The properties are nearly fully leased. The portfolio includes potential for further development with additional building rights.
Industrial zoned land in Södertälje. The zoning plan allows for industrial and logistics development, as well as central services, and fuel and charging services.
Residential property portfolio with five buildings, four freehold and one leasehold. The assets have a total of 181 apartments and 13 retail spaces.

A sale-and-leaseback transaction with Nordic Greens under a new 10-year triple-net lease. The property is situated in Odense, Denmark, and features a combination of office, warehouse, and greenhouse facilities.

The property is located in Södermalm with a mix of residential and commercial spaces. It has good public transportation links, including a new subway station under construction directly beneath the building.
Project Primula consists of two properties located in Kungsbacka, comprising a preschool and an LSS facility. These properties are fully leased to municipal and foundation tenants.
Project Alba consists of an LSS property in Nyköping. These property is leased to Mo Gård.
Located in Möllevången, Malmö, Härden 5 consists of 18 apartments. The property is situated close to Folkets Park and has good access to public transportation.

The property at Tæbyvej 21 is planned for residential and commercial use, with a total leasable area of 7,056 sqm. Tanmia, the developer, have assumed that they can build townhouses on 70% of the site.

Residential development project in Køge, consisting of 64 SFH (2 floors) combined with 42 SFH small residential apartments laid out over 2 stories. The developer expects to have secured legal access to the development rights by June 10th, 2025.
Project Metropolitan comprises eight urban logistics assets in Gothenburg and Stockholm. The portfolio benefits from a diversified tenant mix and has an average site coverage of 40%.

Located in Skarpnäck, the properties are within walking distance of the Skarpnäck subway station, a 20-minute commute to T-Centralen. The buildings include energy-efficient features like solar panels and geothermal heating.
The property contains 51 rented apartments and is located within walking distance of Hakunila's center. The building was completed in 2023 and approx. 100% of the apartments are rented out.
A two-story apartment building with 14 rental apartments. The property is a short walk from the Tuomarila tran station. Approx 100% of the apartments are rented.

Project Carry is a portfolio of last mile logistics and light industrial properties located within a 20 to 30-minute radius from central Copenhagen. The properties have a GLA of 69,400 sqm. Office makes up 18% of the portfolio GLA.

The portfolio comprises ten properties across the Gothenburg and Stockholm-Uppsala regions. The properties are primarily single-let with a diverse tenant mix. There is potential to increase rental income with average in-place rents below market levels and potential from vacancies.

Foldagervej 11 is a newly built warehouse with associated office in Lille Skensved. The property is situated in a commercial area with proximity to local facilities, and with easy access to main roads and the highway.

Sandvadsvej 15A is a warehouse facility with associated office located in Køge, with easy access to main roads and highways. The property is situated in a fully developed industrial district, particularly known for the car and transport industry.

The residential portfolio is located in central Hässleholm. There is considered to be good potential to increase the rents through utility value assessments. The properties have been owned by the same family since the 1960s.

A revitalisation project of commercial two commercial warehouse properties with several buildings in Glostrup. The properties are bought without tenants. Elevate Development will develop the properties to optimise rent.

The property was built in 2004 and comrpises of three condominium units, with Hovedvejen 107 forming unit 1, which includes the entire building facing Hovedvejen. All tenants moved in during 2024 and 2025.

Pasila Tower in Helsinki, near Tripla, was paused in 2022 due to market conditions. Castellum now plans to restart the project with a new concept. The property is currently leasehold, but the plot may be acquired upon completion. The building is planned to be expanded by 5,244 sqm.
Parkhus - Sankt Hans is situated in Roskilde and consists of three buildings. It is a mix of MFR and SFR, such as apartments, duplexes and townhouses.
An opportunity to invest in Ceres Properties which offers exposure to a portfolio of residential properties focused on student and youth housing.

There are currently 60,000 sqm of storage and industrial purposes in the portfolio in Södra Hagalund. Around 210,000 sqm of building rights of mainly housing and commercial premises. The first zoning plan for c. 54,000 sqm has gained legal force.

A portfolio of terraced housing consisting of 960 residential units spread across Jutland, Funen and Zealand. One completed project, with the other ten sites expected to be completed between Q3 2025 and Q4 2027. IRR of 14-19%.
Residential portfolio with key locations in Stockholm, Mälardalen and Malmö. The portfolio consists of 22 properties with 2,496 apartments. Average apartment size of 55 sqm.

Residential development projects across Denmark. The projects comprise a mix of townhouses, apartment buildings and single-family plots. Construction start is in 2025 and have building time ranges from 12 to 16 months.
MFR portfolio consisting of 4 fully let standing assets built 6 months to 2-3 years ago. Located in Rødovre, Glostrup, Herlev and Roskilde.

A commercial property in Glostrup that was previously the headquarters of Paaske Brød. The property is renovated with an invsestment of c. DKK 20M. Approximately 40% of the total area is leased on 5-10 year's non-termination agreements.

The property was acquired by the seller mid-2024 for DKK 35M and is now refurbishing the asset. It is not yet for sale, but could discuss with the seller if there is an opportunity to purchase the property. Price estimate is currently around DKK 80-90M.
A coastal hotel property in Skåne that can be converted for other uses or into exclusive residential housing.

A portfolio of terraced housing consisting of 960 residential units spread across Jutland, Funen and Zealand. One completed project, with the other ten sites expected to be completed between Q3 2025 and Q4 2027. IRR of 14-19%.
Residential building rights for 71 apartments by Stäketsundet. The municipality expects to adopt the zoning plan in Q4 2025, once a new buyer is in place.
Forward sale of a residential property (leasehold) with completion estimated in 2027. The property is located in central Hyllie, 400m from Hyllie station and will include 70 apartments.

Residential building rights of approximately 65,000 light BTA, located near Åkers kanal in Åkersberga. The properties are currently zoned for industrial use, but the seller is working with the municipality on a zoning plan that would allow residential development. Existing cash flow from industrial properties
33 residential units, possible to acquire through a forward-funding deal or submit an offer for the building rights only.
Property located in central Copenhagen, with a leasable area of 1,169 sqm, of which 600 sqm office, 287 sqm retail/café and 282 sqm residential. Espresso house is the largest tenant.
Newly produced residential property at Amager, including 40 smaller apartments (35-59 sqm units)
Portfolio of three assets, two in Brøndby, and one in Ballerup. 40% office, 51% warehouse, 9% other

The property is located in Helsingborg’s South Harbor industrial area. The surrounding area is set for significant development, including the relocation of the Port of Helsingborg and a new container harbour. The existing property will be demolished, the site offers a large-scale development opportunity
Portfolio of 13 residential assets (22 buildings) in HMA. 94% economic occupancy. Potential for leasing optimization and ESG improvements
Located next to Stockholm Central station, formerly housing Casino Cosmopol, now available for redevelopment opportunities
SFR development site in Aarhus of 124,000 sqm sub-divided into three sub-areas with potential for up to 27,000 sqm of lettable area

Development for a Marriott hotel with 110-120 rooms and 12,500 sqm in total, including a supermarket. The location is close to the harbor, just 150m away from a new metro line. Completion estimated Q1 2028
Development of a new office and production facility for SAAB on a triple net lease agreement in Hedenstorp
Forward funding of a property with office premises, laboratories and test facilities, leased to Teknologisk Institut (8,000 sqm), and Agro Food Park (3,500 sqm). Completion estimated Q1-Q3 2027
Logistics property located in Hacksta logistics area in Västerås, let to ICA. The rental income is EUR 83.3M. The property is BREEAM Very Good and meets EPC A
Portfolio of 26 residential properties across Sweden (54% in Mälardalen and 36% in Malmö/Lund). 2,500 apartments in total, with an average build year of 2014

Two modern light industrial assets in the Tampere region (Nokia and Pirkkala). The portfolio includes 11,076 sqm of lettable area and is expected to generate a NOI of EUR 1.3M upon completion of the second asset in April 2026. The properties are fully let with triple-net leases
Two residential properties, 6,300 sqm in Norrköping and 19,390 sqm in Finspång

Development property in central Helsinki, in the Punavuori district. The property was built in the 1960s and is currently leased to the City of Helsinki and HOK-Elanto. The anchor tenant, the City of Helsinki, will vacate the property in 2027. There is development potential for, e.g., residential use, although this will require rezoning
Industrial site in Söderhamn of 25 hectares, with a capacity of 100-150 MW. Land is not zoned. There is an existing factory building of 6,000 sqm on the site
Development project of 123 residential units in Kalundborg
SFR Portfolio including five different projects in different locations (Kalundborg, Ringsted, Odder, Helsinge). Completions in 2026-2027
Portfolio of 4 properties in Jursla, Herstadberg, Ingelsta and Butängen in Norrköping. The properties include warehouse, logistics, some retail and office

Opporuntity to invest in an office conversion project as a club deal. New use: Combination of student, co-living, micro and business apartments. Purchase price of land with existing buildings of EUR 8M. EUR 38M investment in total as a club deal
Rental asset of 284 apartments in central Knivsta. The first phase is completed and fully let since 2023, phase two will be completed in December 2025

column6: L2 Fastigheter, Inter Leisure i Göteborg AB
column16: Property located in Gamlestaden, built in 1925 and 1986. The buildings have been renovated to modern office premises and are leased to 9 different tenants. Potentiall additional building right of 20,000 sqm BTA
Clarion Amaranten (Strawberry) at Kungsholmen. 4th largest hotel in Stockholm in 461 keys and an estimated rental income of SEK 104M
Forward funding or furward purchase opportunity of a residential project in Suviniitty close to Espoo centre.104 residential units with an average size of 45 sqm. Completion H1 2027
Logistics property located in Hacksta logistics area in Västerås, let to ICA. The rental income is EUR 83.3M. The property is BREEAM Very Good and meets EPC A
52,000 sqm land area with potential for 10,400 sqm of resi. No zoning in place yet. Building right price of 2,500 PSM

Data center site in Valle, Norway, with 100MW+ accessible power. The site spans 200,000 sqm, with potential expansion to 400,000 sqm and is approved for industrial use (incl. data center), however, zoning to be completed by new owner - exp. approval H1 2026
7 buildings with 72 student apartments in total, built year 2006. Located on walking distance from the university in Växjö

Prestigous, fully refurbished office property at Erottajankatu in Helsinki CBD. EUR 2.2M in current NOI, estimated EUR 3.1M as fully let. Anchor tenants include e.g., Oras Invest, Norvestor, Trevian, Skanno
Care asset in central Vantaa. Newly built with a WAULT of 18 years

Prime hotel property in Helsinki CBD, directly connected to the metro and surrounded by key commercial and tourist destinations. The asset offers significant value-add potential post-lease through renovation and repositioning. The location benefits from strong tourism growth and high long-term demand.
Newly completed (2025) freehold industrial/logistics asset with 15-year triple-net lease to Scania Suomi Oy. EPC B. Prime location in Aviapolis, Vantaa

The property is located in Helsingborg’s South Harbor industrial area. The surrounding area is set for significant development, including the relocation of the Port of Helsingborg and a new container harbour. The existing property will be demolished, the site offers a large-scale development opportunity
14 semi-detached rental semi-detached houses built 2020, located in Steninge Slottsby. Fully let. Modern standard. No tenant right of possession. The units are leased out for 18,200 SEK per month
Forward sale of 70 rental apartments in Hyllie, Malmö. Expected completion 2027. Leasehold property
Big box retail portfolio with three assets in Lielahti, Tampere. Anchor tenants include Lager157, Puuilo, Minimani, and K-Rauta

The asset will be delivered in 2027 as a modern logistics and production facility. It is leased to a financially strong international tenant under a 15-year triple net lease. The building targets BREEAM Excellent and at least EPC B, and benefits from excellent connectivity within 1 hour of Helsinki and Tampere.
Four properties in Gävle with around 20 different tenants.
Portfolio of four residential assets in Stockholm (Bromma, Hägersten, Enskede). 50 apartments in total, of which 27 are leased on short-term contracts
Portfolio of four assets, located in Karlskoga, Enköping, Strängnäs and Katrineholm. Tenants: Carspect, Mekonomen, Rusta, Dekra, Ahlsell
Two residential buildings in Stockholm (Mälarhöjden and Aspudden). Built year 1944-1949. 32 apartments in Aspudden, 14 apartments in Mälarhöjden
Warehouse/industrial property in Eriksberg. C. 50% vacancy
Forward development project with ~202 apartments, a 1,200 sqm grocery anchor, small commercial space, and a 51-unit cohousing scheme. Construction expected to start summer 2025.
Leashold property in Orminge, Nacka. 114 apartments, completed 2020
Prime logistics portfolio of 18 properties in Lindeberg, Langhus and Vestby in Oslo regio
Portfolio of 4 light industrial assets in Nynäshamn, leased to 11 different tenants. The properties include warehouse, office and retail premises

Corner property in central Östermalm with 16 apartments and four commercial premises, including Restaurang Kommendören. Prestigious address with strong tenant demand. One 130 sqm apartment is currently vacant, offering immediate upside. Rental value of SEK 4.9M
215 newly built rental units in Riksten, Botkyrka. The first phase was completed in April 2025 and is fully let. The second phase was completed in August 2025, leasing is ongoing

Office/industrial building with 19 office units and 10 storage areas plus underground garage; Brandkåren is anchor tenant (25% of rent). There is also an undeveloped land plot of 3,145 sqm with zoning allowing ~6,000 sqm BTA for offices/light industry; pre-approval for hotel concept
Portfolio of 15 institutional-grade assets built 2015–2024 with strong ESG profile (EPC A & B), solar panels, geothermal heating, and 22 tenants in prime locations. Rental value of SEK 77M
211 apartments in central Haninge and Upplands Väsby. Over 11,000 sqm lettable area including three commercial premises
Project of 96 rental apartments (MFR) and 48 BRFs in Lindbacken, outside of Uppsala
Four interconnected office buildings in Gårda, Gothenburg, refurbished 2021–2022, LEED Gold certified, anchored by Telia and other international tenants

62 newly built terraced houses in Helsinge, Nordsjælland, designed with high-quality finishes and sustainable features. Fully let at competitive rents, located near Hillerød and 40 minutes from Copenhagen. The property was acquired for DKK 180 million, corresponding to an initial yield of 4.75%.
34 newly built houses in Kalundborg fully leased to Novo Nordisk Engineering on a long lease, delivered furnished, located in one of Denmark’s strongest growth areas.

31 new single-storey terraced houses in Kalundborg, fully leased to Novo Nordisk Engineering on a long-term contract, built with modern finishes and energy-efficient systems. All units are leased to Novo Nordisk Engineering on a long agreement with a minimum 3-year. lock-in and staggered termination rights. Base rent (DKK/sqm) between DK2,159-2,210.

12 apartments (576 sqm) and one restaurant (144 sqm, leased to Texas Longhorn). Located in Bromma. Built 1942, strong conversion potential as 9/12 units are vacant or short-term, located near Abrahamsberg with good transport links.

Retail park in Tampere region. The property is anchored by K-Citymarket with a 15-year lease and supported by Jula and McDonald’s. Daily services account for 85% of rental income. The retail park, built in 2009, has a BREEAM Very Good rating with a roadmap to Excellent and EPC A.

column6: Bjeredsparken AB (Nordea Liv Fastighet I AB)
column16: Centrally located retail hub in affluent Bjärred, anchored by ICA, Region Skåne, Nordic Wellness and other essential services.

column6: Ringerike Fastighets AB (Nordea Liv Fastighet I AB)
column16: Two modern retail buildings in Malmö’s prime Svågertorp area with strong exposure, tenants incl. Thule, Kvik, Ballingslöv; portfolio certified BREEAM In-Use.

The portfolio comprises six fully let residential properties in central Sundsvall, offering stable cash flow with diversified building ages from late 1800s to mid-1900s. The assets provide secure income while also holding selective value-add potential through refurbishment and attic conversions.
Development project with 71 planned apartments and lakeside location at Mälaren; zoning plan expected adoption in 2025.

Portfolio of three high-end car retail properties in Uppsala and Eskilstuna let to Möller Bil group. Modern assets in prime auto clusters with very long lease terms and guaranteed income, ensuring stability and growth potential in the expanding Mälardalen region.

Large automotive retail property in Uppsala’s Kungsängen cluster with Bilbolaget as anchor tenant. Strong regional draw and excellent visibility, supported by long lease and good technical standard after recent upgrades.
Four residential buildings built 1992/94 with 42 apartments; long tenant tenure and stable cash flow.
Single-property company; 1991-built resi block with 25 apartments and garage; high occupancy.

Two centrally located Malmö residential assets with stable housing demand and parking income. The properties benefit from popular urban locations near Nobeltorget with good transit, and offer potential for further rent increases through ongoing renovation initiatives.

Historic office property in Malmö’s Gamla Staden, fully let to Handelsbanken. Recently refurbished to modern standards and situated next to a planned boutique hotel, offering strong tenant covenant and future upside from the evolving neighbourhood.

Newly built residential scheme in Copenhagen Sydhavn with 333 units and extensive amenities. Fully let with strong demand, ESG-certified and located in a fast-developing urban district with direct metro and S-train access.
Danish residential property “Granskoven”; teaser highlights stable residential income stream.  60 multifamily units and two commercial units.

Historic landmark building originally developed as Stockholm’s largest cinema and later converted to a casino. Currently vacant, the asset offers flexible layouts, prime CBD location at Vasagatan/Kungsgatan, and strong potential for repositioning into office, hospitality, or mixed-use concepts.

Portfolio of two modern industrial/office properties in Librobäck, Uppsala, both ~5 km from central city. Combined leasable area ~2,300 sqm. Tenants include Statens Historiska Museer (government) and local industrial users. Properties in normal condition with stable cash flows.

Modern residential property built 2009 in Kallebäck, Göteborg with 47 apartments (38 regular, 9 BmSS). Includes block lease to Göteborgs Stad for BmSS and antenna contract with Telia. Strong residential location near Korsvägen and Delsjön, stable fully let asset with 28 parking spaces.

A last-mile logistics and wholesale cluster of ~80,000 sqm leasable area, strategically located at Alnabruterminalen in Oslo’s Groruddalen. Anchored by tenants Duri Fagprofil (13,291 sqm, 22.4m NOK rent) and Storcash (10,524 sqm, 19.8m NOK rent). Strong demand drivers with upside from lease reversion, vacancy lease-up (~3,025 sqm vacant), and identified development projects. Net NOI 148.8m NOK (2026E, total).

A portfolio of 5 centrally located residential properties in Halmstad with total 22 apartments. Combined rental income of c. 2.5m SEK, NOI 1.6m SEK. Properties are well-maintained with potential for standard upgrades and future conversion to condominiums.

A consolidated residential portfolio of 10 buildings totaling 97 apartments (~6,400 BOA + 1,400 LOA). Centrally located with stable cash flows. NOI is ~6,500,000 (total rent value (resi+parking+retail) ~10m – costs ~3.5m).

Portfolio of 7 properties in Stockholm suburbs (Täby, Haninge, Huddinge, Lidingö). Anchored by strong tenants including Ahlsell, Ramirent, Preem, and Lixon Holding. Good transport connectivity and strategic industrial locations.

Planned residential area in Vejle with 165 units (107 units are one story terraced houses and 58 are two story terraced houses). Includes landscaped green areas, ponds, and parking. Early-stage project with site plan approved; financials driven by future rental income once built.

Large-scale residential portfolio with 999 apartments across 13 assets in Helsinki metro. Leasable area is 54,133sqm total (53,526 resi + 586 comm). €9.2m fully-let NOI (2026), €8.2m current NOI, €11.7m potential NOI.  Strong fundamentals with 99.9% rent collection, 27% churn, and value-add potential from rent uplift (+6%), refurbishments (+21%), and ESG upgrades. Clear roadmap to EU taxonomy compliance (A–C EPC). Portfolio strategically located near rail links (86% of NOI within walking distance).

Newly built in 2024 in Liljeholmen, Stockholm. Tenants are Internationella Engelska Skolan and City of Stockholm, both on 20-year CPI-indexed leases with municipal guarantee. Facility includes school for 1,200+ students and Stockholm’s largest sports facility with 20,000 annual hours.

Portfolio of 10 lifestyle hotels across Denmark, Germany, and Norway. Includes 928 keys in Denmark, 403 in Germany, and 49 in Norway. Anchored by Copenhagen with pipeline projects in Aarhus and Hamburg. Strong brand in sustainable hospitality.

Two multi-family residential properties in Flysta, Spånga. A total of 23 apartments (1,181 sqm) and 3 premises/storage units (235 sqm) on a freehold plot of 3,041 sqm. Built in 1947–49, with ongoing renovations (roof, plumbing, geothermal heating, solar panels, windows). Possible building rights between the houses. Located in a residential neighborhood close to public transport and Palmérs Park.

Residential-led development in Valby with ~22,100 sqm build rights. Plan includes ~2,950 sqm retail (two supermarkets with long pre-contracts), 6,050 sqm student housing, 5,550 sqm non-profit assisted living, and 7,550 sqm family housing. Attractive location by Vigerslev S-train station, next to Grønttorvet development.

Modern residential rental property built 2008–2018 with 112 apartments and 2 commercial units. Avg. unit size 97 sqm with balconies/terraces, strong location in green setting. Fully let, NOI ~15.7m DKK, priced at 370m DKK (yield 4.53%).
Residential property in Hägersten with 61 units totaling 5,025 sqm BOA. Offered at an asking price of 190m SEK.

Four building-ready plots in Ormsta, Vallentuna, totaling 3,457 sqm. Approved detailed plan with municipal water/sewage connection. Asking price 11m SEK. Suitable for parhus/newbuild project in established residential area with good communications.

Depot Mantorp is a major retail destination along E4 with City Gross as anchor tenant (73% of rental income, lease to 2031). Includes 11 tenants such as Kronans Apotek, Team Sportia, Instabox. Features Sweden’s largest Tesla Supercharger station (40 stalls, +20 contracted). Large expansion potential (40,000 sqm build rights). Recently refurbished (2013, 2023–24). Est. NOI 2025 is 7,733 TSEK and fully rented Est. NOI 2025 is 14,200 TSEK.

Prime residential asset in Hyllie, Malmö. Two newly built buildings (2022) with 85 modern rental apartments, one commercial unit (55 sqm), and parking rights (41 spaces). Certified FEBY Gold & EPC B, with solar panels and smart energy solutions. NOI ~8.8m SEK (2026E). Excellent commuter location 500m from Hyllie station, 8 min to Malmö C and 12 min to Copenhagen Airport.

Portfolio of six residential terraced houses in Rydebäck/Sydvästra Ättekulla, Helsingborg. Built 1990–91, total BOA 503 sqm. Fully let with NOI ~470k SEK, stable single-family housing stock, modern heating systems, and good residential location close to transport and amenities.

Centrally located 1929-built residential property with 38 apartments (avg. 68 sqm) and 6 commercial units. Fully let with NOI ~3.1m SEK, strong residential demand. Extensive renovations 2020–2025 (~5.4m SEK invested) and further upside from “Willhemlyft” apartment upgrades.

Portfolio of two residential properties in Aspudden and Mälarhöjden, Stockholm. Total 46 apartments + 2 commercial units, 2,767 sqm BOA. Combined NOI ~3.2m SEK (2025 fully let). Properties built 1944–49, ongoing renovations, with upside from further apartment refurbishments and attic/basement conversion potential. Short distance to Stockholm CBD (15–18 min).

Portfolio of 5 modern last-mile assets across Stockholm & Gothenburg. Strong covenants with 100% CPI-indexed leases, WAULT 6.2 yrs, occupancy 96%. Reversionary potential >15% and identified development opportunities (e.g. Jordbromalm).

Large affordable housing project in Glostrup with 205 units (193 apartments + 12 terraced houses), 208 parking spaces. Estimated rent of 1,920 DKK/sqm and target exit yield of 4.25% resi and 4.5% parking. Total project cost ~524m DKK. Construction starts 2026, completion 2028. Catella & Nordkranen managing with RAWO as turnkey contractor.

Logistics development site in southern Zealand with 130,000 sqm build rights on 260,000sqm land. Located by E47 motorway, ~1h south of Copenhagen. Strategic hub benefiting from 2029 Fehmarn Belt tunnel. Municipality supportive; sustainability focus with solar rooftops.
Historic Swedish iron foundry site closing in Oct 2025. 22,000 sqm production on 440,000 sqm land. Potential for defense industry, industrial park, or data center (7MW power capacity).

Newly built 2024 office property in Gamlestaden, Gothenburg. Anchored by PEAB, Swisslog, Swedbank, Nordic Wellness, Spaces/IWG, atNorth. PEAB lease guarantee to 95% occupancy. Excellent transport at Gamlestads Torg.

Portfolio of three centrally located office/healthcare assets in Gårda, Gothenburg, totalling 28,112 sqm. Current NOI 40.3m SEK, with potential 78m SEK fully let. Certified LEED Platinum (Gröna Skrapan) and BREEAM (others). Strong connectivity to Ullevi and E6/E20, vacancy upside and stable tenant mix.

Portfolio of 84 newly built apartments across three properties in Steninge Slottsby, Sigtuna. Delivered in 2023 with investment support and energy bonus, modern heating (geothermal) and solar panels, access to 100 parking spaces with EV charging. Strong rental growth with 10.5% negotiated increases in 2024–25, excellent commuter location close to Märsta, Arlanda, Stockholm, and Uppsala.

Major retail development opportunity in Kållered, Gothenburg region, adjacent to IKEA. Property includes 4 buildings with tenants like Coop, Systembolaget, Jysk, STC Gym, Kappahl. Current NOI ~9m SEK, with upside to 34.5m SEK upon full redevelopment. Catchment area 528,000 people, strong population growth, 61,500 daily cars on E6. Large zoning plan (18,650 sqm footprint rights) with strategic potential. 70% vacancy expected 2026.
