Residential portfolio of 8 properties across Stockholm suburbs totaling ~39,000 sqm. Stable NOI of ~61m SEK (2025E) with occupancy ~94%. WAULT ~3.7 years. Diversified tenant base, with upside from rent growth and refurbishments. Efficient management setup through geographically clustered assets.

Well-located logistics/industrial property in Hvidovre south of Copenhagen. Fully let to strong covenant tenant with WAULT ~5 years. Info from 2023: stable cash flow with NOI 1.78 MDKK. Part of established logistics cluster near major transport links.

Coastal residential project in Liguria with build-out of ~120 holiday apartments across multiple blocks. Attractive seaside location in Spotorno, 60 km from Genoa. NOI potential ~3.8m EUR upon stabilization, with target yield ~5.5%. Development upside and strong demand for second homes in the region.

Planned residential project with 132 apartments in 4 blocks on a 9,788 sqm site in Ishøj. Location benefits from proximity to S-train, Copenhagen CBD and Øresund corridor. Sustainable design by Mangor & Nagel Arkitekter, delivery post-2026.

Large-scale residential portfolio of 973 units across 5 high-growth municipalities (Greater Copenhagen, Aarhus, Horsens, Ringsted, Køge). Total ~71,900 sqm GFA, average unit size 73.9 sqm. 39% already completed and fully let, remainder under phased delivery 2026–2027. Strong ESG profile with DGNB certification, diversified tenant demand, and potential rental upside.

Newly built (2021) residential property of 115 apartments with total 6,748 sqm.  An estimation of 4.0% for the annual residential rent increase for 2026 Rents ~20–25% below market at SEK 1,984/sqm. EPC rating B, solar panels, efficient FTX system. Prime location between Malmö and Lund, 5 min from Burlöv station with direct rail to Copenhagen. Strong commuter demand and long-term rent uplift potential after subsidy expiry.

Fully let industrial/office property opposite the metro; a 1973 building on leasehold land with upgrades (geothermal heating, FTX ventilation) and identified potential for residential development in the block.

Industrial property with ~1,300 sqm unused building rights and a 130,000 SEK annual leasehold fee; partially let with opportunity to control the entire block together with neighboring Smälleklingan 2.

1957 apartment building in Slottsstaden (32 units) with central location and stable housing cashflows; noted potential to convert the attic to up to four small apartments. Rental income for 2026 is estimated to reach around SEK 4.3 million and NOI 2026 to reach SEK 3.2 million.

column16: Prime 15,300 sqm retail asset anchored by Rusta, XXL, Arken Zoo in Sisjön retail park. Built 1974/2006 with ~450 parking spaces, strong transport links and catchment area. 90% of rent from A-rated tenants. Rental income 2026E ~30m SEK.

Portfolio of 32 apartments and one elderly care facility (60 beds + 5 apartments) in Karlstad. Central locations in Marieberg and Herrhagen, walking distance to services. Strong tenant covenant with Karlstad municipality for elderly care unit, and popular Willhem-renovated apartments.

120 apartments across 10 two-story buildings in Gråbo, Lerum, with large green courtyards. NOI ~8.2m SEK. Half of units upgraded through Willhem-lyftet, strong demand (5–10 years queue time). Positive planning decision for two new buildings with ~40 apartments (2,830 sqm BTA), potential future upside.

New-build residential project with 186 apartments across ~16,870 sqm (gross). 4–6 story buildings with elevators, underground and surface parking, bicycle facilities, storage rooms, and green landscaped areas. Each apartment has either a balcony or terrace. Built to BR18 energy standards, with district heating, floor heating, and ventilation. Completion targeted post-2025.

Transformation of the former Helsingør Hospital into 165 apartments averaging 90 sqm. Total gross buildable area ~20,125 sqm with underground parking. Strong local rental demand (comparable new builds achieving 2,200+ DKK/sqm, which is the estimated placeholder for base rent). Developer estimates total cost ~483m DKK, with expected exit value ~602m DKK.

Forward purchase of a ~7,300 sqm residential development in Køge Kyst, Søndre Havn. Scheme comprises 85 apartments (avg. 86 sqm) with underground parking (61 spaces) and 170 bicycle spaces. Central waterfront location in a major urban regeneration district. Design includes roof terraces, balconies, and community areas.

Newly built (2022–23) mixed-use property in Steninge Slottsby with 108 rental apartments and 2 commercial units. Total lettable area ~7,758 sqm, NOI ~6.9m SEK (2025E). Strong local demand in Märsta/Sigtuna, supported by new community services and proximity to Märsta station/Arlanda. Modern energy solutions (FTX, bergvärme) in place.

Four residential properties in Ulvsunda, Bromma totaling 70 apartments and 3,535 sqm lettable. Estimated rental value 5.7m SEK (2025), avg. 1,603 SEK/sqm. Attractive location near metro and city, with succession renovation and attic development potential.

Residential portfolio of 294 apartments + 2 preschools across Spånga, Bromma, Tullinge. Total lettable 11,835 sqm, estimated rental value 25.5m SEK (2025). Well-situated in calm residential areas with proximity to services and transport.

Value-add office portfolio of three assets in Västberga (~32,000 sqm). Rental value ~83m SEK with office (73%), retail, restaurant, storage uses. 4 km from Stockholm CBD with strong transport links. Significant upside from lease-up and reversion.

Prime Stockholm CBD hotel investment: Clarion Hotel Amaranten, 461 rooms, fully let to Strawberry on long lease expiring 2035. Includes Brödernas restaurant, garage (47 spaces), and telecom tenants. Recently refurbished with ESG upgrades identified to improve EPC from E to B. Base rent reflects an assumed 2026 rental level.

Turnkey residential development in Ishøj (Greater Copenhagen) with 142 units (avg. 68 sqm) and 142 parking spaces (85 underground). Expected delivery Q1 2027. DGNB Gold certification targeted. Estimated NOI ~17.9m DKK.

Modern industrial production facility built in 2000 and extended in 2023, fully let to Hawo Suomi Oy on a long-term CPI-indexed lease (~10 yrs remaining). Annual rent ~540k EUR (~90 EUR/sqm). Energy class A, total heated net area 4,803 sqm. Strategic location in Liminka, Oulu region, with strong tenant covenant supported by growing Nordic demand for Hawo’s modular timber construction solutions.

Newly built (2023–2025) residential scheme with 125 apartments and two stable commercial tenants (Praktikertjänst, Apoteket). Located in Önsta-Gryta, Västerås with strong demographics and modern energy-efficient buildings.
Pan-European BESS platform with ~12GW pipeline, including operational, under-construction, and shovel-ready assets. Raising £350m equity to support expansion of BESS platform
Fully let light-industrial properties in Södertälje, leased to Scania. NOI 6.3m SEK, lettable area 7,436 sqm. Built 1977 with 2002 extension. Development potential through higher zoning allowance.

Light industrial / logistics property in Tampere’s Lahdesjärvi area with 2,700 sqm lettable space. Built 2004 with 2019 extension, 9 loading doors, 5 m clear height, geothermal heating and solar panels. Stable tenants and strong accessibility near E12/E63.

Grocery-anchored retail centre “Sjötelegrafen” in Nynäshamn with ICA Maxi, Rusta, Dollarstore, Normal & Jysk. 45 tenants, 44,978 sqm land plot. Adjacent to Sweden’s 5th largest harbour with future MAX Burgers site and asset-management upside.

Modern 16-asset grocery and discount retail portfolio across Sweden totaling 72,557 sqm, 93% of income from food and discount tenants. WAULT 6.4 years, fully let, GRI 111m SEK. Anchored by Coop, Rusta, Willys, Dollarstore, Jysk, and others. High ESG standards with newly built assets along key transport corridors (E4, E6, E20, E22).

Fully let gym and sports property leased to SATS Sports Club Sweden AB under a 10-year contract (since 2022). Modernized 2021–22 with geothermal heating, new ventilation, and 73 parking spaces. Located in Täby’s Näsby Slottspark, a fast-growing residential area north of Stockholm.

Discount retail-anchored property in Gothenburg’s strongest retail area, Sisjön. 16 tenants including Rusta, XXL, and Arken Zoo, generating GRI of 36.9m SEK and NOI of 28.0m SEK (2026). Prime visibility, ~450 parking spaces, energy class E, and significant tenant reinvestment (SEK 31m since 2019).

Newly built micro-living project comprising 206 units across 6,681 sqm in Copenhagen. Developed by Nordstern & Fredensborg JV. Gross rental income expected ~23m DKK with NOI ~20.2m DKK upon stabilisation. Energy-efficient (28.7 kWh/m²), 34% rent reversion potential, and strong student housing demand.

Fully let to Migrationsverket under a four-year lease (from Sep 2024). Newly renovated 2022–2024 with 122 rooms, modern amenities, and FTX ventilation. Located next to E18 and Västerås Airport. NOI 6.3m SEK (2025), low OpEx, simple single-tenant operation.

Large-scale residential development opportunity on 39,860 sqm plot in Ekerö. Estimated 45,000–65,000 sqm BTA under new zoning. Owned by ExNord Tappsund AB, plan process currently paused. Valuation basis c. 2,000–2,500 SEK/sqm buildable area.

Portfolio of 419 newly built residential units across 7 locations in Jutland and Funen, built 2023–2024. Fully let modern housing stock with energy-efficient systems (fjernvarme, varmepumper). Total value 767m DKK and average unit sizes 69–126 sqm. Strong regional tenant base.

Fully let 96-unit residential property built 2007 by NCC, EPC A2010. Located next to Delta Park Station (light rail) with 96 parking spaces. Strong rent reversion and privatisation potential, in-place NOI DKK 11.4m, optimised NOI DKK 14.0m. Managed by City Property Holding A/S with stable occupancy and low churn.

Modern retail property in Vantaa’s Tammisto retail hub with 8,966 sqm leasable area. Fully refurbished and extended in 2007, freehold plot with high visibility and 450+ parking spaces. Tenants include daily goods and listed brands. Equipped with solar panels and sustainable energy systems.

Six-property light industrial portfolio south of Stockholm anchored by Bilia AB (92% of rent). 18,077 sqm lettable area, NOI SEK 25.5m (fully let estimate), WAULT 7.9 years, 96% occupancy. Strong ESG and solar upgrades, located along National Road 73 with redevelopment potential in Albyberg.

Two adjacent residential buildings in Solna with 75 apartments (4,375 sqm), of which 24 units (1,356 sqm) are vacant or short-term let. Annual rent income 8.4m SEK (2025). Begärt pris 220m SEK. Newly built Miljöbyggnad Guld–certified education and sports complex in Liljeholmen/Midsommarkransen, Stockholm. Anchored by Internationella Engelska Skolan (IES) and City of Stockholm on 20-year CPI-indexed leases (exp. 2044). Leasehold, next ground rent renegotiation 2032.

Large mixed-use development project adjacent to Vigerslev Allé Station in Valby, Copenhagen. 22,100 sqm total including 7,550 sqm family housing, 6,050 sqm student housing, 5,550 sqm elderly care (VIBO), and 2,950 sqm retail pre-let to Rema 1000 & another supermarket on 15-year leases. Mixed-use development project in Vanløse comprising hotel (6,000 sqm), serviced apartments, retail, restaurant, and fitness (total GLA 18,000 sqm). Strategically located in central Vanløse near metro and strong residential base.

Three-storey 1958 residential property on leasehold plot (3 681 sqm) with 34 flats and 6 small commercial units. 24 apartments vacant for new owner after renovation (2025). Total rent SEK 5.2 m, NOI SEK 3.9 m.

Nordic Swan eco-certified rental scheme with 71 apartments and 2 commercial units and 37 parking spaces in Upplands Väsby. Lettable area 3 762 sqm, expected completion Q4 2027. Forecast NOI SEK 10.4 m (2 762 SEK/sqm) based on 2027 estimates. Yield of 4.8% for forward purchase.

National portfolio of six modern industrial and logistics assets in southern and central Sweden. Tenants include DHL, Bring and PostNord. Strong ESG profile with solar installations and new-build standards.

Portfolio of seven planned residential projects (all rowhouses) across Greater Copenhagen totaling ~1,096 homes and ~97,000 sqm building rights. No social housing component planned. JV model: capital partner funds land and construction.

Large-scale DGNB Gold-certified residential development in Næstved comprising 277 units (~71 sqm avg.), incl. senior housing, townhouses, and apartments. Land area 56,703 sqm, building rights 19,846 sqm. Building permit secured; revised version under review (8 weeks processing). Mix of family, student, and senior living with shared amenities. Construction 15–24 months with staged delivery.

Historic 1906 building in prime Östermalm location comprising 28 apartments, 5 offices, 3 retail units, 1 hotel (Pärlan), and 5 storages. Excellent location near Östermalmstorg with long-term value-add potential through lease-up and minor upgrades.

Institutional-grade Swedish grocery and discount retail portfolio with 16 fully let assets totaling 72,557 sqm. Tenants include Coop, Willys, Rusta, Dollarstore, Jysk, and Jula. WAULT 6.4 years, GRI 112m SEK, NOI 96m SEK (2026). 93% of income from grocery/discount retailers. Modern buildings (2018–2025) with ESG upgrades; 80% EPC A–C. Located along E4, E6, E20, E22 corridors in strong regional retail hubs.

Large-scale redevelopment project in Åkersberga comprising future residential building rights (~70,000 sqm BTA: 65,000 residential, 5,000 commercial) on 44,214 sqm land. Planning in early phase with municipal forstudie approved April 2025; existing 11,780 sqm lettable industrial area at 98% occupancy.

Institutional-scale forward purchase residential portfolio totalling 71,794 sqm / 974 units across five Danish growth cities (Horsens, Aarhus, Ballerup, Ringsted, Køge). Estimated NOI DKK 95.7m. Single-tenant office property located in Ballerup. Let to Atea Danmark A/S on a lease with 4 years unexpired term (since 2013). Strategically located light industrial property in Sollentuna, close to E4. Built 1973–85, 6,141 sqm lettable area with 15 tenants. Big-box retail property centrally located in Hyvinkää. Built 1985, EPC C. Fully let to Power (electronics), Hyria Foundation, and Kesko (grocery). NOI €0.6m from €0.75m GRI, WAULT 5 years. Mixed-use residential and retail property (1,371 sqm residential, 1,258 sqm commercial) in Tyresö Strand comprising 18 apartments and one Coop grocery store (lease until March 2028). Built 2003 by HSB, EPC B. Estimated 2026 NOI ~5.3m SEK on rent value ~6.2m SEK. Option to convert 3 attics into 28–30 sqm studio apartments.

Forward development comprising 227 residential units (185 student housing, 42 flats) and a 1,504 sqm healthcare facility pre-let to Lyngby-Taarbæk Municipality on a 15-year NPI-indexed lease. Total GLA 12,152 sqm plus 81 parking spaces. Expected completion Dec-2028, gross rent DKK 32.0 m and NOI DKK 27.1 m (≈2,234 DKK/sqm). Located next to Lyngby Stadium, within the “Five-Finger Plan” corridor and near DTU University.

Newly built (2025) prime retail park in Bro, anchored by strong grocery and discount tenants (Willys, Lidl, Rusta, Dollarstore, Apotek, Stadium Outlet, Normal). Located along E18 with catchment of 1 million within 30 minutes, population growth +30% (2014–2024).

Prime last-mile logistics and distribution facility built in 1999. Currently 32% let to Carlsberg Danmark A/S, 51% to PostNord A/S (lease ends March 2026), and 17% vacant. Sale structured as asset deal.

Institutional Danish light-industrial and logistics portfolio of 18 assets totalling 169,666 sqm. 58% light industrial, 33% hub logistics, and 9% other. WAULT 2.8 years, 96% occupancy. Modern single-tenant logistics and HQ facility built 2014 with expansions 2018 & 2021 for Båstadgruppen AB. GLA 11,512 sqm on 47,528 sqm plot, freehold. 10.5 m clear height, 8 loading docks, solar panels (1,500 sqm), and new zoning plan (Sept 2025) allowing +5,500 sqm expansion. Strategic location along E6/E20 motorway near Helsingborg logistics cluster.

Newly constructed build-to-rent residential development of 149 terraced houses totalling 15,721 sqm (averaging 106 sqm per unit), developed by Bennu Development ApS. Phase 1.1–1.3 completion expected Q4 2025–Q1 2026. Fully market-rent exempt under Danish Rent Act. Located in southern Kolding near the new Ringvej Syd with strong infrastructure and growing residential demand.

Modern retail property located at the entrance to Åkersberga, anchored by Stora Coop (59% of rent) and ÖoB (21%), complemented by Arken Zoo and smaller tenants. Built 2012 with Max Burgers pad-site added 2021. 420 parking spaces incl. 5 EV chargers. Potential for 3,600 sqm BTA expansion and tenant rotation for health/fitness use. Strategic retail location with 1.4m annual visitors, upgraded façade and EV stations in 2024.

Residential investment platform with 39 properties (1,047 rental units) valued at SEK 1.84bn. Portfolio concentrated along the E4/E6 corridor from Helsingborg to Stockholm. LTV 58%. 93% residential, 7% commercial. Current pipeline includes Helsingborg (355 apartments, SEK 530m). Management targets IPO by 2028 with SEK 5bn AUM.

Three freehold industrial properties totaling 18,035 sqm lettable area on 44,329 sqm land, fully let to 13 tenants incl. Domino , Ryds Glas, Leo’s Lekland, and more. Guaranteed rent 2.9m SEK (2028–2030) and new 15-year Domino lease. Major renovation (fixed-price 37m SEK, completion Dec 2027). Potential +3,000–3,500 sqm building rights (2027 plan update). Long-term potential for tenant repositioning and school spin-off for higher yield.

Large education and light-industrial property centrally located in Rødovre near Rødovre Centrum. Comprises 12,188 sqm on 16,549 sqm land, with workshop halls (4–5 m height), offices, and cafeteria. Zoned for mixed use under Kommuneplan F506 (potential for housing conversion). Seller may lease back temporarily post-sale.

17,228 sqm industrial and education complex on 43,000 sqm land. Built 1966 (renov. 2006). Located between Ring 3 & 4, with high accessibility and potential expansion rights (70% density). Energy label D. Zoned under Lokalplan 5.1 allowing workshop, teaching, and industrial use. Guide price DKK 120m (6,965 DKK/sqm).

9,070 sqm flexible business and educational complex on 22,034 sqm land, close to Herlev Station and the upcoming light rail. Built 1961/1973. Asking DKK 75m (8,269 DKK/sqm). Area designated for future residential redevelopment under Herlev’s Marielund plan. Energy labels C–D.

Modern last-mile light-industrial and office property of 8,326 sqm let entirely to Miele A/S on a short-term lease. Annual rent DKK 5.39 m (647 DKK/sqm), net DKK 4.99 m after costs. Strategic location 12 km from Copenhagen CBD near E47 and Motorring 3. Built 1974/1987 on 12,000 sqm plot with 2,368 sqm offices and 3,320 sqm warehouse basement. Potential for re-letting or multi-tenant conversion.

Mission-critical airport logistics hub occupied by DHL Supply Chain, Freight & Global Forwarding. Built 2006 (41,700 sqm: 21,100 warehouse, 12,100 cross-dock, 8,600 office) on 115,700 sqm freehold plot with 14,800 sqm unused rights. 600 kWp solar panels and geothermal heating to achieve BREEAM Very Good / EPC A. Location adjacent to Ring Road III and Helsinki Airport runways

column6: Bro Mälarstrand Bostad AB (Magnolia Bostad & KF Fastigheter JV)
column16: Development opportunity within the new Bro Mälarstrand district, offering 18,600 sqm BTA of residential rights (~125 townhouses, avg. 130 sqm). All groundwork and infrastructure completed, zoning plan final since 2018, and ownership freehold. Located lakeside near Bro Hof Slott Golf Club, with access to E18 and commuter rail. Fully serviced plots, ready for construction.

column6: Kasper Andersen Invest ApS & S.A.M.G.L Holding ApS
column16: Modern 7,073 sqm logistics and office property built 2017/2020, fully let to Link Logistics A/S. Features 1,444 sqm offices and 5,629 sqm warehouse with 7 dock doors, 8 ground-level gates, and solar panels. Located in Odense SE industrial park with 1,200 sqm future building rights. Sold as company share deal.

Residential portfolio comprising 8 assets (266 apartments). Average apartment size 51 sqm, 98% occupancy. Built between 1934–2022; 62% of GLA in modern (post-2017) buildings. Freehold tenure (7/8 assets), energy classes B–E. Strong demand across prime Helsinki Metropolitan Area, portfolio positioned for privatization and rent uplift .

Large-scale data centre development project on 145 hectares freehold site in Robertsfors, northern Sweden. Planned for 250–280 MW capacity, powered by 100% renewable energy via Skellefteå Kraft (SE2 zone). Phased delivery: Step 1 – 70 MW (2029), Step 2 – 280 MW (2031). Zoning approval expected Q4 2026, construction-ready 2027. Located 45 min from Umeå and 70 min from Skellefteå with access to E4 and 95% fibre coverage.

Contemporary 129-unit residential property built 2006 in the “Fuglekvarteret” of Copenhagen NV. In-place rent 2,347 DKK/sqm p.a., NOI DKK 13.94m, stabilised NOI DKK 19.29m (+38%). EPC B. Fully let, 34 parking spaces (15 basement, 19 street). Rental reversion potential 33%. Constructed on 1971 basement, freehold, sold as share deal.

127-unit micro-living property located in Domus Vista, an iconic Copenhagen landmark tower. GLA 5,206 sqm, avg. unit 41 sqm, fully let, EPC B. Built 1969 (redeveloped 2018). In-place rent 2,545 DKK/sqm, NOI 11.76m DKK, stabilised 13.52m DKK (+15%). sale structured as share deal. Located in Frederiksberg near CBS and Frederiksberg Centret.

523-unit residential portfolio in central Boden totalling 40,521 sqm. Stable ~97% occupancy and 2026 NOI of SEK 31m. Strong rent-reversion potential (often +15–33%) and several assets with commercial units or development potential. Concentrated locations close to town centre, transport, and services.

Fully let 10,400 sqm mixed hotel-retail asset anchored by Scandic Meilahti (188 rooms) and HOK-Elanto grocery store. Completed 2016 with modern ESG profile. Long fixed hotel lease (14 years at signing) provides secure cash flow; NOI approx. €2.85m. Prime location next to Meilahti Hospital Campus with strong institutional tenant profiles.

Danish residential build-to-rent portfolio comprising Golfhaven, Grøndals Have and Stenlængepark with total GLA 17,852 sq m and current NOI c. 25.7m DKK. The assets provide modern family and senior housing in growth towns south of Copenhagen.

Social infrastructure portfolio in Tygelsjö, Malmö consisting of three community-use properties (preschools and LSS housing) totalling 2,645 sq m. Fully let with WAULT ~11.8 years and forecast 2026 NOI c. 5.6m SEK at 100% economic occupancy.

Mission-critical life-science campus in Gladsaxe Business District with 3 main tenants: Zealand Pharma, Ferrosan Medical Devices and Jespers Torvekøkken. Total GLA 33,115 sqm and annual base rent 25.2m DKK. 99.5% let to blue-chip biotech/med-tech and food-service tenants with significant fit-out, supporting strong stickiness and future rent reversion potential.
Former Falck station in Hørsholm converted to residential use and fully re-let in 2024. Comprises 16 residential units with a total area of 1,739 sqm and potential for unit sales and rental uplift.

Modern residential scheme in Greve comprising 184 units developed 2017–2019 with 12,780 sqm residential floor area and in-place rental income of ~23m DKK. Average unit size 69.5 sqm with efficient layouts, 204 parking spaces and BREEAM In-Use “Good” certification. Residential reversionary potential of ~9.6% is indicated in the teaser.

column6: Jernhusen Holding 10 AB (via Jernhusen Stockholm 161 AB)
column16: Freehold last-mile logistics development site of 11,422 sqm land with 14,965 sqm BTA building rights (zoning plan in place). Located in Östberga, Stockholm’s premier logistics cluster near DHL, PostNord, Bring and Årsta Intermodal Terminal. Only 10 min from Stockholm C and 5 min from E4/E20. One of very few remaining freehold plots for modern logistics close to the city.

Freehold industrial/warehouse land with >100,000 sqm lot size and 10–15k sqm buildable/lettable area. Rental income approx. 8.5m SEK, current occupancy 50–70%. Zoning allows residential, industrial, social infrastructure, providing strong development potential.

Fully let high-spec industrial/lab building leased to Element Materials Technology on a long triple-net lease. 6,994 sqm, NOI 15.0m SEK, WAULT 11 yrs, modernized 2022. Located next to Linköping Airport in a strong engineering cluster.

Portfolio of four Danish courthouses fully let to the Danish State (Bygningsstyrelsen) with state-guaranteed income. Total lettable area 26,532 sqm. Stabilised NOI across assets after capex increases significantly (Sønderborg 6.6m, Nykøbing 6.9–7.9m, Hjørring 4.5m, Næstved 12.3m). All assets undergoing or planned refurbishments with negotiated lease extensions to 10–20 years.

Sale-and-leaseback portfolio of ~120 critical infrastructure stations (fire, ambulance, emergency response, health services). Total net rent approx. 50m DKK, estimated acquisition price 645m DKK, net yield 7.5–8%. Long 10+ year leases expected, triple-net structure, fully occupied nationwide strategic response-time locations.

Newly built 200-unit residential portfolio (completed 2020–2021) located in central Märsta next to Märsta Centrum and commuter rail. Total area 9,689 sqm, 2026 rent value 25.9m SEK, forecast NOI 21.0m SEK (2,167 kr/m²). Modern spec with high-quality interiors; one building certified Miljöbyggnad Silver. Portfolio sold via share deal (Fastpartner Märsta Holding I AB).

Residential portfolio of 119 apartments across five buildings built in 1972, totaling 9,041 sqm lettable area. Located in a quiet, nature-oriented area surrounded by forests and close to lakes. Transaction to be executed as a share deal, with indicative bids due 21 January 2025.

High-quality residential development consisting of 20 semidetached single-storey homes (parhus), each 90 sqm, 4 rooms, energy class B and premium specifications. Norm rent ~2,500 SEK/sqm (~18,826 SEK/month per unit). Indicative forward value ~4.9m SEK per unit (≈98m SEK total).

Large-scale residential development opportunity on Orust, within walking distance to the sea and with exclusive boat berths tied to the property. The land can support minimum 100 units (villas, townhouses, semidetached houses, and smaller multi-family blocks).
Newly built residential project in Mälarporten with 119 units, BOA 7,413 sqm, and 92 parking spaces. Modern, energy-efficient design in a major redevelopment area close to transit and services.
Residential new-build scheme in Viksäng consisting of 168 units, BOA 10,309 sqm, and 108 parking spaces. Phased completion 2025–2027. High specification with green energy profile.

Platform acquisition covering 816 residential units in Vallentuna region. Total BOA 48,597 sqm, LOA 1,938 sqm, 461 parking spaces, and a 2026 NOI of SEK 130.15m. Mix of completed and forward-funded assets with strong rental demand and modern energy standards.

Fully leased logistics/warehouse property on an 11,358 m² freehold plot. Rent 3.61m DKK, NOI 3.26m DKK. Lease begins 1 Jan 2026 with 5-year mutual non-termination. Modernised asset with LED lighting, office upgrades, and documented handover standards.

Large-scale residential development area in Egedal with ~36,000 m² buildable rights plus 2,200 m² commercial hub and 594 m² senior living. Zoning in place, infrastructure partly completed, and excellent regional connectivity (5 min to Egedal station, 30 min to Copenhagen).

New heavy industrial hall leased entirely to Nordic Tank Oy under a capital lease, indexed to CPI with minimum +2% annual increases. Tenant may purchase the asset during the first 3 years at 5.7–5.9 M€. Free height >10 m, steel structure relocated from Pyhäjoki nuclear site.

Centrally located mixed-use property in Vasastaden, comprising 6 residential apartments, 3 office units, and 2 restaurant units. Total lettable area 1,210 sqm (51% residential). Built 1882, freehold ownership. One apartment and two office units leased without security of tenure, enabling conversion to residential, optimisation of offices, and potential attic development. Transaction intended as a share deal.

Residential portfolio of 9 centrally located properties in Katrineholm comprising 122 apartments and 11 ancillary units. Total lettable area 8,334 sqm, of which 94% is residential. Estimated rental value ~11.7m SEK (2026). All assets located within 2 km of Katrineholm Central Station. Transaction structured as a share deal.

Forward-funded residential development in Sollentuna developed by JM, comprising 165 apartments with an average unit size of 57 sqm. Total lettable area 9,352 sqm, estimated rental value ~29m SEK (2027). Construction started Q2 2025, completion expected Q1/Q2 2027. Target Nordic Swan certification and EPC B. Includes 93 parking spaces in mobility house.

Combined residential portfolio comprising 689 apartments across three new-build assets: Barkarby (409 units, 18,347 sqm NLA, completed 2025) and two Spånga assets (280 units, 14,189 sqm NLA, completion 2027). Total NOI 2026 ~SEK 104.4m, 100% EU Taxonomy aligned, freehold tenure, strong public transport access and modern residential standards.
Off-market portfolio of five light-industrial assets proposed to be sold together in one transaction. Assets located in Greater Copenhagen (Hvidovre, Hedehusene) and Southern Jutland (Vamdrup).

Newly constructed residential property in Ballerup, Greater Copenhagen, comprising 153 apartments across 11 buildings with total GLA 11,059 sqm and 134 parking spaces (69 underground). Construction completed early November 2025 with all units let at completion. High ESG standard (A2020 EPC), strong residential demand, approx. 18 km from central Copenhagen.

Portfolio of four newly built logistics assets (completion 2022–2025) located in Vestby and Moss, approx. 30–40 minutes from Oslo.  Strong ESG profile (EPC A–B, BREEAM-NOR Very Good). Rent reversion potential of 15–20%, mainly in Vestby.

Fully let industrial/warehouse and office property in Länna Industrial Area, offered via share deal. Modern technical standard including floor heating, air-to-water heat pump, and recently approved OVK.

Prime last-mile/logistics property in Avedøre Holme offered with full vacant possession, enabling refurbishment and/or redevelopment. IM indicates potential to utilise ~15,000 sqm additional building rights (buyer to assess).
Newly built residential scheme with 153 units across 11 buildings plus 139 parking spaces (incl. 68 underground) in landscaped “park-like” surroundings. EPC A2020; sale structured as a share deal.
